cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.CC. 

The paper deals with the problem of simultaneous geometric embedding of planar graphs, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry and graph theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also discusses the weak rectilinear realizability of abstract topological graphs, which is related to graph drawing and topology, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Additionally, the paper involves combinatorial optimization and complexity analysis, indicating that it could also fit into cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
